  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Beach</strong></span></p>
<p>Guests of the Residence Esplanade can use one of two beach clubs that are just a couple of minutes’ walk from the hotel. Enjoy the swimming pool on the beach or relax on the loungers while enjoying the sea views. Guests can use these facilities free of charge from around 30 May to 12 September. Please note that most beach clubs here require guests to wear bathing caps when in the pool. <span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Spa</span></strong></p>
<p>Just next door to the hotel, you'll find the Suite 62 SPA, which is perfect for those seeking out a moment of relaxation and tranquillity. They have an extensive choice of massages and treatments available as well as a Thermarum area with a Finnish sauna and Turkish bath, all payable locally. </p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Activities</strong></span></p>
<p>The hotel is a great base for cycling holidays as a member of Italy Bike Hotels. The region has fantastic routes of varying levels for road bikers and mountain biking. What's even better is that Residence Esplanade is geared up with everything you need to get out cycling while you're away. They know the area really well so can give you advice on the best cycling routes as well as provide maps and GPS - so whether you're a professional cyclist or just fancy a leisurely bike ride in beautiful surroundings, they'll be on hand to advise. You can hire bikes directly from the hotel, starting from around €25 per day, payable locally. They have everything from racing bikes to e-bikes and a spacious bike storage room, with repair shop too. </p>
<p>Golf enthusiasts will be spoiled for choice here, with lots of courses close to the hotel. Versilia gold club has and 18 hole course, PAR 71, set in a beautiful wooded landscape, The Cosmopolitan 18 hole course, PAR 72, is right on the coast, so you get beautiful sea views as you play or for a challenge, check out the Montecatini Terme 18 hole course. Speak to the helpful reception staff or the booking office to book a round while you're in resort, payable locally. </p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>General Facilities</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
